f a fridge", "thumbnail_url": "http://sourceforge.net/p/yomo/screenshot/yomosfg.png/thumb", "url": "http://sourceforge.net/p/yomo/screenshot/yomosfg.png"}, {"caption": "Energy consumption of a radiant heater", "thumbnail_url": "http://sourceforge.net/p/yomo/screenshot/yomosfg2.png/thumb", "url": "http://sourceforge.net/p/yomo/screenshot/yomosfg2.png"}, {"caption": "YoMo Arduino Shield", "thumbnail_url": "http://sourceforge.net/p/yomo/screenshot/YomoSoldered.jpg/thumb", "url": "http://sourceforge.net/p/yomo/screenshot/YomoSoldered.jpg"}, {"caption": "YoMo blank Arduino shield", "thumbnail_url": "http://sourceforge.net/p/yomo/screenshot/YomoNotSoldered.jpg/thumb", "url": "http://sourceforge.net/p/yomo/screenshot/YomoNotSoldered.jpg"}], "short_description": "Researches have shown that immediate feedback can increase energy saving dramatically. YoMo aims to empower people using low-cost open hardware smart meters in their household. The metering system consists of a coordination unit, a raspberry pi, and several smart meters, arduino boards equipped with communication shields and our self-designed yomo metering shield. \r\n\r\nThe smart meters are attached to household devices and monitor their energy consumption. The gathered data is timestamped and transmitted to the coordination device. This device offers interfaces to control the smart meters. On top of the software runs a apache webserver that provides all estimated data on our yomo project homepage. \r\n\r\nThe system does not need any maintenance and works out of the box after the devices were integrated into the housholds Wi-Fi network.\r\n\r\nLink to the scientific paper:\r\nhttp://arxiv.org/abs/1409.3404\r\n", "shortname": "yomo", "socialnetworks": [{"accounturl": "", "socialnetwork": "Twitter"}, {"accounturl": null, "socialnetwork": "Facebook"}], "status": "active", "summary": "You Only Meter Once - The open hardware smart metering system", "tools": [{"label": "Activity", "mount_point": "activity", "name": "a